{"lemma":"كِسْرَةُ","slug":"كِسْرَةُ","root":"ك.س.ر","root_slug":"ك-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-س-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36964","n36965","n36970","n36971"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"kasra (a vowel in Arabic signifying an /i/ sound)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"instance noun of كَسَرَ (kasara)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fragment","examples":[{"text":"أَعْطِنِي وَظِيفَةً مَعَ ٱلْأَحْبَارِ لِآكُلَ كِسْرَةَ خُبْزٍ","english":"Give me a job with the priests that I may eat a fragment of bread."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a type of flatbread","tags":["Morocco"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Instance noun of the verb كَسَر (kasar, “to break”)."},"ipa":["/kas.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36964","headword_ar":"كَسَرَهُ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, &c.,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsrhu","text_ar":"اكتسرهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the latter signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he broke it off:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iqotaTaEahu","text_ar":"اـِقْتَطَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like and signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he broke it off for himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for] you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu TarafFA","text_ar":"مِنْهُ طَرَفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsrtu","text_ar":"اكتسرتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I broke off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke off for myself, from it, an extremity"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) You say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotuhu A@nokisaArFA","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُهُ ا@نْكِسَارًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_inokasara kasorFA","text_ar":"اـِنْكَسَرَ كَسْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", putting each of the inf. ns. in the place of the other, because of their agreement in meaning, not in respect of being trans. and intrans. (Sb, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusira","text_ar":"كُسِرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his leg broken; his leg broke."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yakosiru Ealayoka Alfuwqa","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَكْسِرُ عَلَيْكَ الفُوقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroEaAZa","text_ar":"الاَرْعَاظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yukas~iru","text_ar":"يُكَسِّرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in the CK, * and in a MS copy of the K, but we find the former reading in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rEZ","text_ar":"رعظ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the K,) [lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one breaks against thee the notch of the arrow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the sockets of the arrow-heads:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a one is angry with thee:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is vehemently angry with thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rEZ","text_ar":"رعظ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which see further explanations.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusira bayonahumo rumoHN","text_ar":"كُسِرَ بَيْنَهُمْ رُمْحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A spear was broken among them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a quarrel occurred among them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Reiske, cited by Freytag, but whether from a classical author is not said; and explained by him as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Simultas inter eos intercessit."},{"kind":"text","text":")] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara AlkitaAba","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY Eid~api A^abowaAbK wafuSuwlK","text_ar":"عَلَى عِدَّةِ اَبْوَابٍ وَفُصُولٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He divided the book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing, into a number of chapters and sections"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara Al$~aEora","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الشَّعْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke the measure of the poetry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not make the measure of the poetry correct."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotu Alqawoma","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broke, crushed, routed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"defeated, the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotu xaSomiY","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُ خَصْمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I defeated my adversary"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b9-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara nafosahu","text_ar":"كَسَرَ نَفْسَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdued, his spirit."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b10-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abased,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"humbled, himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotu mino saworatihi","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُ مِنْ سَوْرَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abated, somewhat of his impetuosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyranny,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anger"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara Humay~aA Alxamor biA@lomizaAji","text_ar":"كَسَرَ حُمَيَّا الخَمْر بِا@لْمِزَاجِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abated, the intoxicating influence of the wine by the mixture"},{"kind":"text","text":"of water]. (A.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara","text_ar":"كَسَرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino barodi AlmaA='i","text_ar":"مِنْ بَرْدِ المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Har~ihi","text_ar":"حَرِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. and inf. n. as above, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He abated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allayed, somewhat of the coldness of the water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"its heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aikosiro Ean~aA","text_ar":"اِكْسِرْ عَنَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwbapN","text_ar":"رُوبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b15-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara AlEaTa$a","text_ar":"كَسَرَ العَطَشَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It abated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"allayed, thirst."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara mataAEahu","text_ar":"كَسَرَ مَتَاعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2611},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sold his goods by retail, one piece of cloth after another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K:) because, [on the contrary,] wholesale makes them to find purchasers readily. (TA) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasarotu Alr~ajula Eano muraAdihi","text_ar":"كَسَرْتُ الرَّجُلَ عَنْ مُرَادِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I turned the man, averted him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned him back, from his desire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakosiru *anabahu","text_ar":"يَكْسِرُ ذَنَبَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoda maA A^a$aAlahu","text_ar":"بَعْدَ مَا اَشَالَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contorts his tail after raising it"},{"kind":"text","text":"], said of a camel. (K.) ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara Alv~awoba","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aljiloda","text_ar":"الجِلْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He folded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he creased, the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the skin."},{"kind":"text","text":"Ex. of the former signification, [in which the pronoun refers to a tent:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Hayovu yukosaru jaAnibaAhu","text_ar":"مِنْ حَيْثُ يُكْسَرُ جَانِبَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where its two sides are folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) You say also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara AlwisaAda","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الوِسَادَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He folded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubled, the pillow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cushion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reclined, upon it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAsirN","text_ar":"كَاسِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara jafonahu","text_ar":"كَسَرَ جَفْنَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naHowahu","text_ar":"نَحْوَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He blinked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he wrinkled his eyelid"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh. art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gmz","text_ar":"غمز"},{"kind":"text","text":".) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN HaAr~apN takosiru AlEayona Har~FA","text_ar":"رِيحٌ حَارَّةٌ تَكْسِرُ العَيْنَ حَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hot wind, that makes the eye to blink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contract and wrinkle the eyelids, by reason of heat"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xwS","text_ar":"خوص"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara Eayonahu","text_ar":"كَسَرَ عَيْنَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara mino Tarofihi","text_ar":"كَسَرَ مِنْ طَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. and inf. n. as above, (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He contracted"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~a","text_ar":"غَضَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyes;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to wrinkle the lids;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in which sense the former phrase is used in the present day:] (K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara EalaY","text_ar":"كَسَرَ عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarofihi","text_ar":"طَرْفِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he contracted"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaD~a","text_ar":"غَضَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his eye,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eyes, somewhat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [or perhaps"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here a mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY~a","text_ar":"عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which case we must read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tarofahu","text_ar":"طَرْفَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so that the meaning would be as above with the addition"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mukaAsarapu","text_ar":"مُكَاسَرَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEayonayoni","text_ar":"العَيْنَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmugaADanapu","text_ar":"المُغَاضَنَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the contracting of the eyes so as to wrinkle the lids"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gDn","text_ar":"غضن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara AlT~aAy^iru janaAHayohi","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الطَّايِرُ جَنَاحَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara","text_ar":"كَسَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, (S, A, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusuwrN","text_ar":"كُسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or in this case, when the wings are not mentioned,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusuwrN","text_ar":"كُسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[only]; which shows that a verb, when its objective complement is forgotten [or suppressed], and the inf. n. [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadiyvu","text_ar":"الحَدِيثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in my original I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHadavu","text_ar":"الحَدَثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] itself is desired [to be expressed], follows the way of an intrans. verb; (A;) [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is by rule the measure of the inf. n. of an intrans. verb, of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala","text_ar":"فَعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEada","text_ar":"قَعَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quEuwdN","text_ar":"قُعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jalasa","text_ar":"جَلَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"juluwsN","text_ar":"جُلُوسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEolN","text_ar":"فَعْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"of that of a trans. verb;] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bird contracted his wings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracted them somewhat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that he might descend in his flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in order to alight."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b22-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasara AlHarofa","text_ar":"كَسَرَ الحَرْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pronounced the letter with the vowel termed kesr:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he marked the letter with the sign of that vowel."},{"kind":"text","text":"A conv. phrase of lexicology and grammar.]       -A2-  See also 7."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","A","IAar","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n36965","headword_ar":"كسّرهُ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takosiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) is with teshdeed to denote muchness [of the action] or multiplicity [of the objects] (S) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He broke it much, in pieces,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into many pieces:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many times,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repeatedly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he broke it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning a number or collection of things.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yukas~iru Ealayoka Alfuwqa","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يُكَسِّرُ عَلَيْكَ الفُوقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroEaAZa","text_ar":"الاَرْعَاظَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1. ―         -b3-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ks~rhu","text_ar":"كسّرهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He divided it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(i. e. a number, and a measure,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"into fractions."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ks~rhu AlkaraY","text_ar":"كسّرهُ الكَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Drowsiness made him languid"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hyD","text_ar":"هيض"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-  ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ks~r $aEarahu","text_ar":"كسّر شَعَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takosiyrN","text_ar":"تَكْسِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He crimped his hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raT~ala","text_ar":"رَطَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ks~r AlmaA='u AlwaAdiY","text_ar":"كسّر المَا=ءُ الوَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water made"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusuwr","text_ar":"كُسُور"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the turnings, bendings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"windings,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaATif","text_ar":"مَعَاطِف"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the valley, and the parts thereof eaten away by torrents, to flow with water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n36970","headword_ar":"كَسْرَةٌ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A defeat."},{"kind":"text","text":"You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa Ealayohimu Alkasorapu","text_ar":"وَقَعَ عَلَيْهِمُ الكَسْرَةُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Defeat befell them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasorN","text_ar":"كَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n36971","headword_ar":"كِسْرَةٌ","root":"ksr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(in some copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisorN","text_ar":"كِسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but this is a mistake, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of a broken thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece broken from a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fragment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"broken piece, of a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisarN","text_ar":"كِسَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisorapN mino Alxubozi","text_ar":"كِسْرَةٌ مِنْ الخُبْزِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A broken piece of bread."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusaArN","text_ar":"كُسَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}